# Spark — Cursor project rules (index only)

**Do not duplicate** stack, Liquid Glass, or architecture detail here. Authoritative sources:

| Topic | File | When applied |
|-------|------|----------------|
| **Product philosophy & role** | `.cursor/rules/ios-product-philosophy.mdc` | Always |
| Liquid Glass / materials | `.cursor/rules/ios-liquid-glass.mdc` | Always |
| Swift 6, concurrency, security | `.cursor/rules/ios-foundation.mdc` | Always |
| SwiftUI patterns | `.cursor/rules/ios-swiftui.mdc` | `**/*.swift` |
| Design / a11y / localization | `.cursor/rules/ios-design-system.mdc` | `**/*View*.swift` |
| Performance | `.cursor/rules/ios-performance.mdc` | Manual |
| New feature module | `.cursor/rules/ios-module-scaffold.mdc` | Manual |

## Human docs (not AI rules)

- Agents onboarding: `AGENTS.md`
- Contributing: `docs/CONTRIBUTING.md`
- Design philosophy: `docs/DESIGN_PHILOSOPHY.md`
- Architecture: `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`
- Architecture & packages: `docs/PACKAGES.md`
- API for backend: `docs/API_CONTRACT.md`
- Local dev / Mock: `docs/DEVELOPMENT.md`
- CI: `docs/CI.md`
- Git: `docs/GIT_WORKFLOW.md`

## Persona

Repo role + design philosophy: **`ios-product-philosophy.mdc`**. Extended Alex persona may also live in Cursor Settings → Rules; on UI scope conflicts, **product philosophy wins**.
